The paper deals with dynamic pricing in an online setting, which is a common problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of high-dimensional feature vectors and the unknown and changing parameters of the valuation model suggest that the paper may belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The objective of maximizing revenue also suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-category of economics and computation (cs.EC). The use of historical sales data and the characterization of regret suggest that the paper may belong to the sub-category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) or information theory (cs.IT).
